-385786790.text: "The increased phosphorylation and accumulation of p53 may lead to mitochondrial apoptosis by upregulating and derepressing proapoptotic members of the bcl-2 family, such as bax, bak, bad, bid, puma and so on, while on the other hand downregulating and repressing antiapoptotic members, such as bcl-2, bcl-xl, Mcl-1 and so on."
